'''Bryan Bickell''' (born March 9, 1986) is a [[Canada|Canadian]] professional [[ice hockey]] player currently playing for the <!--[[Rockford IceHogs]] of the [[American Hockey League]] (AHL), the top [[farm team]] of the--> [[Chicago Blackhawks]] of the [[National Hockey League]].
==Playing career== Bickell grew up playing minor hockey in his hometown of Orono, Ontario for the Leafs rep program before playing AAA for the Central Ontario Wolves organization.
For his Bantam season, Bickell moved to the Toronto Red Wings of the GTHL for one season before being drafted in the 2nd round (36th overall) in the 2002 OHL Priority Selection by the Ottawa 67's. Bickell was a member of the Bantam All-Ontario champions Toronto Red Wings with future Chicago Blackhawk teammate [[Dave Bolland]].
Bickell was drafted 41st overall in the [[2004 NHL Entry Draft]] by the [[Chicago Blackhawks]] from the [[Ottawa 67's]] of the [[Ontario Hockey League]] (OHL). After his junior career, Bickell was signed to a 3-year entry level contract with the Blakhawks on June 5, 2006. He made his professional debut with the [[Norfolk Admirals]] at the beginning of the [[2006â07 AHL season|2006â07]] season.
